 of globalization, the varying forms of secularism in Western states, and the different kinds of relations between states and religious institutions in the historical traditions and contemporary politics of Islamic, Indic, and Chinese societies. They also examine the limitations and dilemmas of governmental responses to religious diversity, and grapple with the question of how secular states deal (and should deal) with such pluralism. This volume brings in perspectives from the non-Western world and engages with viewpoints that might increase states' capacities to accommodate religious diversity positively.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aReligion and politics. 0aReligion and state. 0aReligious pluralismxPolitical aspects. 0aSecularismxPolitical aspects. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh1 aAbu-Laban, Yasmeen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaman, Lori G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerman, Bruce J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerman, Bruce J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBeyer, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhargava, Rajeev, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhargava, Rajeev, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBramadat, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBray-Collins, Elinor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCouture, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrake, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuru, Ahmet T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaliberté, 